lenders.name: Oleg
lenders.loan_because:
Oleg is 57 years old. He was born and lives with his family in Yerevan city. Oleg is married and has two sons. One son is a student at Yerevan State Economical University and lives in Yerevan. Oleg's family is engaged in agricultural business and farming in Vanadzor city.

 For many years Oleg, himself, has been a butcher. He rented a stall in a Yerevan food market and sells meat and meat products. Twice a week, Oleg buys meat from farmers and wholesale markets in Lori Province, and he resells it in his stall in Yerevan food market. With the profits from his meat trading, Oleg meet his family's needs and pays his son's tuition fees.

 Oleg has a big dream, to organize his own cattle breeding and to sell meat from his own farming. He has a plot of land near his house, and he decided to construct a barn for animals. For realization of his dream, he knows that he must work hard and accumulate money. Now, Oleg needs to borrow 2,000,000 Armenian drams (5000.00 USD). He will use the loan to buy a large amount of meat from wholesale markets to resell, and three piglets with which to begin his animal breeding activity.
